algebra.solution:
Substitute 5 for $b$ in the expression defining $a*b$ to find that $a*5=2a-25$.  Setting this equal to 9, we find  \begin{align*}
2a-25&=9 \implies \\
2a&=34 \implies \\
a&=\boxed{17}.
\end{align*}

We apply the order of operations.  To see that this means to sum the denominator first, note that we can write the expression as \[1 + 2/\left(3 + \frac{4}{5}\right).\] So, we have \begin{align*}
1 + \frac{2}{3+\frac{4}{5}} &= 1 + \frac{2}{\frac{15}{5} + \frac{4}{5}}\\
&= 1 + \frac{2}{\frac{19}{5}} \\
&= 1 + 2\cdot\frac{5}{19} =1 + \frac{10}{19}=\frac{19}{19} + \frac{10}{19} = \boxed{\frac{29}{19}}.
\end{align*}

When using the distributive property, we add the product of 16 and $2x$ to the product of 16 and 5:

\begin{align*}
16(2x+5) &= 16\cdot 2x+16\cdot 5\\
&= \boxed{32x+80}
\end{align*}

